To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: @tarbyparty has unlocked the secret to the fluffiest Ramos Gin Fizz ever. The @deathandcompany co-owner uses an iSi nitrous oxide (N2O) cream whipper, a kitchen gadget typically used to produce and dispense soft cheeses or whipped cream, to create this "light-as-air" rendition. But the RGF is far from the only drink that benefits from a whipped cream dispenser. The nitrous oxide technique works for any recipe that calls for a protein component, such as egg whites, cream or aquafaba—think traditional sours, flips and even eggnog. Head to the link in our profile—and swipe right—to see how it's done. #drinkpunch 📷: @dylanandjeni

node.text: The smash—spirit, sugar and mint served on crushed ice—was built for summer. Considered the cooler, more effortless sibling of the julep, it's refreshing, simple, and delicious. node.text:
Meet Sam Miller (@samson_miller), a member of our Bartender in Residence Class of 2021.⁠
⁠
The @paganidolsf bartender and founder of @b4.change has a clean, modern take on tropical cocktails—and a vision for a more equitable industry. He's bartended across the West, from Park City to Honolulu, San Francisco to Denver, driven by a mission to secure greater representation for BIPOC in the industry. “I want to see more people of color running bar programs and in upper-management positions,” says Miller. His spirit-forward tropical and tiki-style cocktails are bursting with fresh ingredients. Head to the link in our profile to get to know @samson_miller in three drinks. #bartenderinresidence #punchdrink⁠
⁠
📷: @kellypuleio

node.text: The original Kitty Highball simply calls for equal parts red wine and ginger ale, but in this modern take by @freshkillsbar, the ginger ale is replaced with fresh ginger syrup and soda water. Get the recipe for this low-ABV riff of the 1940s cooler via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: You now have an excuse to sip on a Negroni in the morning. @5shakes' breakfast-ready take on the classic, dials back the booze and adds freshly-squeezed peach juice to mimic the a.m. style of a Bellini. For the bitter component, he drops the Campari in favor of Cappelletti Vino Aperitivo. Get the slightly lower-proof recipe for the Negroni Alla Fiama via the link in our profile.  #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Angostura takes center stage in this spicy riff on the Piña Colada. Based on the structure of a traditional Piña Colada (rum, pineapple and coconut), @zacoverman replaces most of the rum with Angostura bitters. A bit of lime and overproof rum smooth out and balance the lip-curling bitters, while pineapple and cream of coconut maintain the Piña’s tropical spirit. node.text: Break the rules, stir with pineapple. 🍍 Chief among cocktail-making doctrines is the dictum that drinks with juice are shaken, those without are stirred. But for @alsotack, there are times when it makes sense to push back. “In old recipes, almost never is the technique listed for you,” says Sotack. “The whole idea of stir or shake a cocktail is ambiguous in almost every source.” He believes in this approach so firmly that he devoted an entire section of @jupiter_disco’s latest zine, Preservation, to “Stirred Drinks But With Pineapple.” Head to the link in our profile to learn more about how to incorporate pineapple and other fruit juices into stirred drinks. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Forget that we're halfway through July and make an Endless Summer, or as @sometimes.y calls it, a "Negroni on vacation." The simple, four-ingredient cocktail combines the big three—Campari, gin, sweet vermouth—with an ounce of pineapple juice. Shaken and served over ice, this drink can easily be scaled up into a large-format cocktail. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @_mediumraw
